demonstrates proficiency in ELA based on the student scoring within the fiftieth
percentile on the most recently administered universal reading screener approved by the
state board of education or the Tennessee universal reading screener; and
SECTION 3. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
